==English==
===Etymology===
French ''[[empêcher]]'', [[hinder]], from Latin ''[[impedicare]]'', [[fetter]]

===Verb===
'''to impeach''' ([[impeaches]], [[impeached]], [[impeaching]])

#To [[hinder]].
#To bring a legal proceeding against a public official, asserting that because s/he committed some offense, s/he should be removed from office.
#To discredit an individual or group with presumed expertise.

